8 An Act relating to broker compensation; amending 59
O.S. 2021, Section 858-359, which relates to payment
9 to broker; authorizing offer of compensation for
certain services; providing certain exceptions; and
10 providing an effective date.
11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 59 O.S. 2021, Section 858-359, is
15 amended to read as follows:
16 Section 858-359. A. The payment or promise of payment or
17 compensation by a party to a broker does not determine what
18 relationship, if any, has been established between the broker and a
19 party to a transaction.
20 B. In the event a broker receives a fee or compensation from
21 any party to the transaction based on a selling price or lease cost
22 of a transaction, such receipt does not constitute a breach of duty
23 or obligation to any party to the transaction.
24
